
    TODAY would
have been the 93rd birthday of the Pan Africanist Congress founder Robert
Sobukwe.The former
Wits lecturer and anti-apartheid struggle activist, was born the 5th of
December 1924 at Graaff-Reinet, in the Eastern Cape.In 1949, he
was elected as the National Secretary of the ANCYL, he then grew through the
ranks of the ANC to eventually become the secretary of the ANC’s Standerton
